cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use this proof or its verification artifacts, please cite this
  repository and the prior lower-bound work identified in the literature review.
title: "Four exact finite Zarankiewicz numbers"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "GPT 5.6-Sol"
version: 1.1.0
date-released: 2026-07-04
repository-code: "https://github.com/dfield/finite-zarankiewicz-closures"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - Zarankiewicz problem
  - extremal combinatorics
  - K3,3-free bipartite graph
  - formal verification
  - SAT certificates
abstract: >-
  Reproducible proofs that Z(9,23,3,3)=103, Z(10,21,3,3)=106,
  Z(10,22,3,3)=110, and Z(11,20,3,3)=111, accompanied by explicit extremal
  matrices, independent verifiers, exact arithmetic certificates, deterministic
  SAT/MIP models, a Lean arithmetic audit, and an explicit 37-case open frontier.
